HEADWORD: Sibilancy
<hw>Sib"i*lan*cy</hw>
<pr>(?)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>The quality or state of being
sibilant; sibilation.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Milton would not have avoided them for their <qex>sibilancy</qex>,
he who wrote . . . verses that hiss like Medusa's head in wrath.</q>
<rj><qau>Lowell.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sibilant</ent>⟦br⟧
